cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on semantic role labeling (SRL) using neural network models. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also incorporates ELMo embeddings, which are a type of deep learning model, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper explores the relevance of linguistic structures in deep learning models, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses CoNLL-2005 shared task data, which involves natural language processing and could also be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) since NLP and computer vision often overlap in research.
